The '''A.D. Xenopol Institute of History''' ({{lang-ro|Institutul de Istorie „A.D. Xenopol”}}) in [[Iași]] is an institution of research in the field of [[history]] under the auspices of the [[Romanian Academy]]. The institute was named in honour of Romanian historian [[Alexandru Dimitrie Xenopol]].
The institute was founded in 1941 as the "A.D. Xenopol Institute for the History of Romanians" within the [[Alexandru Ioan Cuza University]], by Professor [[Ilie Minea]], and became an independent entity in 1943 (as the "A.D. Xenopol Institute of National History").<ref>[http://adxenopol.academiaromana-is.ro/istoric.html Istoricul Institutului]</ref> In 1970 it was renamed the "A.D. Xenopol Institute of History and Archaeology", and placed under the authority of the [[Academy of Social and Political Sciences of the Socialist Republic of Romania]].<ref>[http://adxenopol.academiaromana-is.ro/istoric.html Istoricul Institutului]</ref> After the [[Romanian Revolution|fall of the Communist regime]] and the disbandment of the Academy of Social and Political Sciences, the Institute is passed under the aegis of the [[Romanian Academy]]. The archaeology section splits off, forming the [[Iași Institute of Archaeology]], and the institute acquires its present name.<ref>[http://adxenopol.academiaromana-is.ro/istoric.html Istoricul Institutului]</ref>
==See also== *[[Romanian Academy]] *[[Iași Institute of Archaeology]]
