{{Infobox University |name = Institute for Political Studies - Catholic University of Portugal |image = |motto = |established = 1997 |type = [[Private school|Private]] |president = |director = João Carlos Espada |chairman = |faculty = |profess = |staff = |city = [[Lisboa]] |state = |country = [[Portugal]] |address = Palma de Cima, 1649-023 Lisboa, Portugal |campus = |free_label = |free = |website = [http://www.iep.lisboa.ucp.pt/ www.iep.lisboa.ucp.pt] }}
The '''Institute for Political Studies''' ({{lang-pt|Instituto de Estudos Políticos}}, '''IEP''') of the [[Catholic University of Portugal]] ({{lang-pt|Universidade Católica Portuguesa}}, '''UCP''') is a Portuguese research institution focusing on [[political science]] and [[political philosophy]]. It was created on 1 September 1997 at the [[Lisbon]] campus of the Catholic University of Portugal. The IEP was the only Portuguese think tank to get nominated for the top Think Tanks of World, according to [http://www.fpri.org/research/thinktanks/GlobalGoToThinkTanks2008.pdf The Global "Go-To Think Tanks": The Leading Public Policy Research Organizations in the World, 2008], published by the Think Tanks and Civil Societies Program of the [[University of Pennsylvania]].
